      "author": "github-actions[bot]",
      "description": "## рҹҰ• A quick polish pass\n\n3.5.0 brought the alias autocomplete вҖ” 3.5.1 makes it squeaky-clean for the Obsidian plugin review, and sneaks in a genuinely nicer settings experience while it's at it.\n\n### рҹ”Қ Settings you can search\n\nLinkosaurus adopted Obsidian 1.13's new declarative settings API. Every option now shows up in Obsidian's **global settings search** вҖ” try typing \"autocomplete\", \"blocklist\", or \"delimiter\" into the settings search box and jump straight there. On older Obsidian versions the classic settings tab keeps working as before.\n\nAs a bonus, delimiter validation now shows up as a friendly inline message right under the field, instead of a toast notification.\n\n### рҹ§№ Under the hood\n\n- The suggestion popup's gliding pill now positions itself through Obsidian's sanctioned styling API (`setCssStyles`) вҖ” the one thing the automated plugin review flagged as an error.\n- The README title is a proper Markdown heading, so automated checks can match it against the manifest.\n- Obsidian API typings pinned to `^1.13.1`.\n\nNothing about linking itself changed. Happy linking. рҹҰ•\n\n\n**Full Changelog**: https://github.com/polygonhunter/linkosaurus/compare/3.5.0...3.5.1",
