      "author": "github-actions[bot]",
      "description": "## рҹҰ• Your aliases now finish themselves\n\nThe big one this release: **alias autocomplete**. Start an inline alias, and a little glass panel floats in beside your cursor, suggesting the target before you've typed it.\n\n```\nUrlaub//Bв–Ң\nв”Ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ\nв”Ӯ рҹ”— Berlin        в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ рҹ”— Bielefeld     в”Ӯ\nв””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ\n```\n\nArrow keys to choose, **Enter** to link вҖ” `[[Berlin|Urlaub]]` lands fully formed. No trailing space, no typing out `ielefeld`.\n\n### вңЁ What's inside\n\n- **Fuzzy search** вҖ” suggestions are drawn live from your note names, keywords, and frontmatter aliases; `Bln` still finds Berlin, and mappings show where they lead (`ML вҶ’ Machine Learning`).\n- **Zero extra keystrokes** вҖ” selecting a suggestion writes the finished wikilink immediately.\n- **A popup that knows its place** вҖ” it only appears inside the alias syntax (`//` and `///`, including your custom delimiters). Normal typing stays popup-free, URLs and code blocks stay untouched, and Esc dismisses it without a trace. It never picks for you: type the alias out by hand and everything works exactly as before.\n- **Dressed for the occasion** вҖ” frosted-glass panel, a selection pill that glides between entries, and keyboard hints in the footer (`вҶө link В· esc dismiss`). Matches your theme in light and dark; on phones it steps back to the platform's flat look.\n- **One toggle** вҖ” not your thing? *Settings вҶ’ Alias target suggestions* turns it off.\n\nCloses #10. Happy linking. рҹҰ•\n\n\n**Full Changelog**: https://github.com/polygonhunter/linkosaurus/compare/3.4.6...3.5.0",
